# GitButler and multi-editor handoff

Full policy: [`docs/decisions/gitbutler-multi-editor-workflow.md`](../../docs/decisions/gitbutler-multi-editor-workflow.md).

Maintainer often **starts in Claude Code** and **continues in Cursor** on the same
`task/*` branch when context runs out. Treat branch + PR state as truth, not the
prior chat.

## Start of session (always)

1. `git branch --show-current` and `git status -sb`
2. If on `gitbutler/workspace`: `but status -fv` (GitButler mode — use `but` for writes)
3. Check for existing PR: `gh pr view --head $(git branch --show-current)` or `gh pr list --head …`
4. Do not recreate branches or run `but setup` without reading current state

## Plain git vs GitButler (one mode per clone per work period)

| Mode | Writes |
| --- | --- |
| Normal branch (`task/*`, `main`) | `git` / `gh` per `AGENTS.md` |
| `gitbutler/workspace` | **`but` only** — no `git commit`, `git checkout`, `git merge`, `git push` |

After GitHub merges to `main`: in But mode run `but pull --check` then `but pull`.
When But work is done for a while: `but teardown --checkout-to main`.

## GitButler hygiene (But mode)

- **Many unapplied branches OK** (parked features); **applied stacks:** prefer **1** for test/handoff, **2** only if file-disjoint integration
- Test another feature: `but oplog snapshot` → unapply current → apply target → test → restore (see policy doc *Parallel development + isolated testing*)
- Before commit on shared files (`pyproject.toml`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`):
  `but unapply` other applied stacks → commit → re-apply only if needed
- One virtual branch ≈ one future PR; do not bundle unrelated scope
- Use `but diff` → `but commit <branch> -m "…" --changes <ids>`; do not chain `but` mutations with `&&`
- Delete stale lane: `but apply <branch>` then `but branch delete <branch>` (delete fails on unapplied lanes)
- History edits: `but rub <source> <target>`; mode pick in policy doc (parallel / stack / worktree)
- Stale lanes: `but oplog snapshot` before bulk cleanup; runbook `docs/runbooks/gitbutler-workspace-cleanup.md`
- Push: `but push <branch-name>` then PR (`but pr new` or `gh pr create`)

## Handoff to next editor (Claude ↔ Cursor)

Before ending: **commit everything**; note branch, HEAD SHA, open PR URL, remaining checklist.

Incoming editor: verify branch/PR; run smallest relevant tests; do not assume the other tool ran `but pull`.

## Worktrees

Use a separate worktree when two agents need isolation or the same hot files concurrently.
Primary clone: prefer either But **or** plain git for a given session — not mixed writes.
